1.  pwd                 (present working dir)
2.  cd                  (change dir)
3.  mkdir t1            (To create the dir)
4.  rm -rf dir/filename (To delete the dir/file)
5.  cd ..               (To return 1 step back from the dir)
6.  vi filename         (To create the file)
7.  i                   (instert mode to enter the content)
8.  esc shift : wq      (To save the content inside the file)
9.  esc shift : q!      (To unsave the changes inside the file)
10. cat > file name     (To create the file)
11. touch filename      (To create the file)
12. nano filename       (To creat the file)
13. cntrl x and y enter ( To save the content in the file)
14. cat filename        (To display the content of the file)
15. cp -r               (source-path to dist-path)
16. *                   ( To select all)
17. mv                  (To rename the file/ To move the file/dir from source to dist)
